# Azure Authentication
#
# AUTOMATIC CONFIGURATION:
# If you've configured azlin with Azure CLI, this file is auto-generated
# when you run `npm start` for the first time. The PWA pulls config from:
#   - Tenant ID: `az account show` (Azure CLI)
#   - Subscription ID: `az account show` (Azure CLI)
#   - Bastion name/RG: ~/.azlin/config.json (azlin config)
#
# CLIENT_ID requires manual setup (see docs/pwa/getting-started.md Step 4)
#
# NOTE: Auto-generation NEVER overwrites existing .env file.
#       Your manual customizations are always preserved.
#
# If automatic config fails, fill in values manually below:

VITE_AZURE_TENANT_ID=your-tenant-id
VITE_AZURE_CLIENT_ID=your-client-id
VITE_AZURE_SUBSCRIPTION_ID=your-subscription-id
VITE_AZURE_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000

# Azure Bastion (auto-configured from azlin if available)
# VITE_AZURE_BASTION_NAME=your-bastion-name
# VITE_AZURE_BASTION_RG=your-bastion-resource-group
